# Technologies:
- Use Bun:
  - as the TypeScript runtime
  - to serve a HTTP and/or WebSocket API
  - to connect to databases using their SQL libraries
- Database:
  - Use Postgres

# Testing
- Use bun when writing tests as well as their test runner

# Coding Standards
- Prefer types over interfaces
- Use proper TypeScript types for all variables, functions and return types
- Use barrel imports
- Implement proper error handling and input validation
- Always use relative imports
- Use async/await for asynchronous operations

# Best Practices
- Ensure secure, efficient code following RESTful API best practices
- Respect SOLID principles
- Focus on performance and readability
- Validate all user input